Nm found it! Checking now.

Hi Zahra, 


I checked the pixel from the test url and initially I had a difficult time find a product in stock to add to cart and test the purchase flow. The item I ended up purchasing actually took me to jcpenny.com:

 Otherwise, on the staging site I see:

A ViewContent event is firing on the landing page. I would expect to only see a PageView event here:

on a product detail page, I was able to see a ViewContent event fire, which is perfect. But there were no content parameters included there:

The advertiser should add those parameters per the instructions here.


I added an item to the cart, but no AddToCart event fired:

Please ask if there is an item on the test site that is definitely in stock so I can test that (this was on the production site, so possibly disregard).


From the data I was able to pull for the staging site, in lieu of testing on the staging site, I am seeing that for CompletePayment, Email is reporting which is great. But no parameters for content are reporting:

they will want to add those.

For AddToCart, I am seeing content parameters reporting well. They should duplicate this for CompletePayment:

For ViewContent, Email format is invalid, and content id is missing:

PlaceAnOrder - missing content id.


Attaching report.


Thanks, Heidi
Thank you for prioritizing this!! I sent this to the client and I'll let you know if they have follow up questions.

Hi Zahra, great! I'll keep this ticket open for now. Also, do let me know if they have a specific in-stock product on the staging site I can check CompletePayment with.


Have a great weekend!


Heidi

Hi Heidi, 


Here's a response from the client, do you mind taking another look?


I have made some adjustments to the Tik Tok pixel in the test environment.

Here are my responses

  1. I have moved the view content to the PDP/mini pdp page only and it has the content parameters for the product.
  2. Cart add is firing with content item data as well. They can try this product to add to cart: https://dt-test4.jcpenney.com/p/gold-toe-athletic-sport-6-pair-crew-socks-mens/1c41ac6?pTmplType=regular&catId=SearchResults&searchTerm=socks&productGridView=medium&dpAkamaiOverride=1
  3. For the payment and order placement events, it has content as well now.
  4. For the email, we are passing a sha256 email in the identity event, so it is already hashed on our end.

 

They can give it a try again and let me know if there are any follow-up questions/issues.


Thanks!!

Hi Heidi, 


One more thought here, can you check that they're ready to run VSA from a pixel POV?


Thanks!

Hi Zahra, yes will check again now!


Heidi

What I'm seeing looks very good overall. The funnel of events is as follows:

PageView

ViewContent

AddToCart

PlaceAnOrder

CompletePayment

Required parameters are reporting well, where applicable (content_id, content_type, content_name, price, quantity, currency).


Events to add, in case they might want to optimize toward these events in the future (nice to have but not required):

CompleteRegistration - when I complete adding all my name/address/phone details here:

Great work!


Heidi

https://www.jcpenny.com/

Account ID - 7085451312208429057

Implementation Type: Pixel only

-Events: Upper to lower funnel:

PageView - fires on home page and collection pages - great!

ViewContent - fires on Product Detail Pages:

parameters in 'contents' array all displaying as expected. Example:

[{"content_id":"ppr5008290601","content_name":"adidas womens lightweight track jacket","quantity":1,"price":"0.00","content_category":"coats & jackets","brand":"adidas"}] - perfect!


AddToCart - did not fire when I expected it to. Example:

Could you please call this to their attention?


InitiateCheckout - I would suggest they add this here:


AddPaymentInfo - I would still suggest they use this event this when billing info is added. This is the page that loads after I entered my payment info and submitted, event could be triggered by that button click:

or when this page loads:

CompletePayment - is not firing for me now:

this was working before. Could you ask them what happened?


AM: Automatic and Manual Advanced Matching - not applicable until CompletePayment is firing again


Thanks, Heidi
